com.helger.jcodemodel

Class JTypeWildcard

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJType
      • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJClass
        • com.helger.jcodemodel.JTypeWildcard
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJGenerable, IJObject, IJOwned

    public class JTypeWildcard
extends AbstractJClass
    Represents a wildcard type like "? extends Foo" or "? super Foo".

    Instances of this class can be obtained from AbstractJClass.wildcard(EWildcardBoundMode)

    Our modeling of types are starting to look really ugly. ideally it should have been done somewhat like APT, but it's too late now.

    Author:
    Kohsuke Kawaguchi
